<Window x:Class="EchoForge.StartPopup"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        Title="Welcome" Height="400" Width="600" WindowStartupLocation="CenterScreen" ResizeMode="NoResize">
    <Grid Margin="10">
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="*"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
        <Image Source="/resources/wflogo.png" Height="80" Stretch="Uniform" HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
        <ScrollViewer Grid.Row="1" VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,10,0,10">
Welcome to EchoForge<LineBreak></LineBreak>
by NovelSmith Shop<LineBreak></LineBreak>

Hi, and thanks for checking out EchoForge – a free, professional-grade audiobook narration tool built specifically for independent authors.<LineBreak></LineBreak>

This software was developed entirely by one person – Christopher Schlosser – out of a passion for storytelling and a desire to help fellow writers bring their stories to life through sound.<LineBreak></LineBreak>

If you find EchoForge helpful, please consider:<LineBreak></LineBreak>

💬 Joining our Discord server (linked in the Settings tab) – a space to ask questions, share feedback, and connect with fellow authors.<LineBreak></LineBreak>

🍵 Supporting development with a donation – every bit helps me keep this and other author tools alive and growing.<LineBreak></LineBreak>

📚 Exploring my published novels on Amazon – your interest in my writing means the world.<LineBreak></LineBreak>

Thank you again – and happy forging.<LineBreak></LineBreak>

— Christopher Schlosser
Developer and Author
            </TextBlock>
        </ScrollViewer>
        <Button x:Name="CloseButton" Grid.Row="2" Content="Close (10)" Width="80" Height="30" HorizontalAlignment="Center" IsEnabled="False" Margin="0,10,0,0" Click="CloseButton_Click"/>
    </Grid>
</Window>